h1. set-version

h2. Purpose

Sets the current application version inside the application metadata file (@application.properties@)

h2. Examples

{code:java}
griffon set-version 0.6
{code}

h2. Description

Usage: 
{code:java}
griffon set-version [number]
{code}

* @StatusFinal@ - When the version has been set

When executing Griffon retains metadata about the currently executing application inside the IGriffonApplication object. The version of the application is one such item of metadata.
